IN
THE
DISCHARGE
OF
RELIGIOUS
DUTIES.
Martin,
having
known
the
taste
of
excitement,
wanted
a
second
draught;
having
felt
the
dignity
of
power,
he
loathed
to
relinquish
it.
Miss
Helstone
that
girl
he
had
always
called
ugly,
and
whose
face
was
now
